  "markdown_debrief": "### SHARP 4.0 Cognitive & Surgical Debrief\n\n> **💡 Cytokines are proteins; PAF is a lipid.**\n\n---\n\n## S — Set the Stage\nThe incorrect statement is that Platelet-Activating Factor (PAF) is a major cytokine. While PAF is a potent inflammatory mediator with significant effects on platelet aggregation, bronchoconstriction, and vascular permeability, it is fundamentally a lipid mediator, not a protein-based cytokine.\n\n## H — Highlight Excellence\nCytokines are a broad category of small proteins or peptides that are crucial for cell signaling, particularly in the immune system. They mediate and regulate immunity, inflammation, and hematopoiesis. Their actions are diverse, including direct effects on target cells, and they often exhibit synergistic or antagonistic interactions, potentiating or inhibiting each other's functions. Understanding the distinct biochemical nature of inflammatory mediators is key to their classification and therapeutic targeting.\n\n## A — Address the Gaps\n\nOption A (Incorrect): This statement is actually correct. Cytokines do act directly on target cells via specific receptors and often exhibit synergy, meaning they can potentiate each other's actions.\nOption B (Incorrect): This statement is also correct. IL-1 is a well-established major proinflammatory cytokine with multiple systemic effects, including contributing to skeletal muscle proteolysis in catabolic states like sepsis or severe injury.\n\n## R — Review Learning Points\n\n| Mediator Type | Examples | Chemical Nature |\n|---|---|---|\n| Cytokines | IL-1, TNF-α, IL-6 | Proteins/Peptides |\n| Lipid Mediators | PAF, Prostaglandins, Leukotrienes | Phospholipid derivatives, fatty acid derivatives |\n| Chemokines | IL-8, MCP-1 | Small proteins |\n\n## P — Plan (Board Pearl)\nBoard Pearl: PAF is a lipid mediator, not a cytokine.\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Imaging & Intraoperative Pearl\nN/A\n\n## 📋 Guideline Anchor\nN/A\n\n---\n\n### Answer Breakdown\n| Option | Text | Status |\n|--------|------|--------|\n| A | Cytokines act directly on target cells and may potentiate the actions\nof on | ❌ Incorrect |\n| B | Interleukin 1 (IL-1) is a major proinflammatory mediator with\nmultiple effe | ❌ Incorrect |\n| C | Platelet-activating factor (PAF) is a major cytokine that results in\nplatel | ❌ Incorrect |\n\n**✅ Answer: UNKNOWN) ** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Difficulty: Medium** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Source: 699910936-MedCosmos-Surgery-MCQ-General-Surgery.pdf**\n",
