  "question": "47. It is stated that enteral nutrition is safer than parenteral nutrition. Which of the following may be complications of enteral nutrition?",
  "options": {
    "A": "Hyperosmolar, nonketotic coma.",
    "B": "Vomiting and aspiration.",
    "C": "Pneumatosis cystoides intestinalis.",
    "D": "Perforation and peritonitis."
  },
