  "answer": "AC) Wound contraction is carried out by highly specialized cells\ncalled myofibroblasts, which, as their name implies, have histologic\ncharacteristics of fibroblasts and smooth muscle cells. The activity of\nthese cells, and therefore wound contraction, can be influenced by\ntopical application of smooth muscle inhibitors such as thiphenamil.\nInhibitors of microtubule formation in myofibroblasts, such as colchicine\nand vinblastine, also inhibit wound contraction under experimental\nconditions. Glucocorticoids and NSAIDs do not affect the wound\ncontraction process.",
