  "question": "251 Which of the following result in a decrease in functional residual capacity?",
  "options": {
    "A": "Shallow breathing",
    "B": "Partial airway occlusion",
    "C": "Absorption atelectasis",
    "D": "Hemothorax"
  },
  "answer": "a, b, c, d) A decrease in functional residual capacity is caused by incomplete alveolar inflation related to 1) shallow breathing; 2) partial or complete airway occlusion, which may be generalized (as in bronchospasm) or localized (as in gastric aspiration); 3) absorption atelectasis, which occurs when oxygen is substituted for nitrogen in the inspired gas; or 4) conditions in which air or fluid is occupying a potential alveolar space in the chest such as pneumothorax, hemothorax, or pulmonary edema.",
  "chapter": "Review",
